<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet" integrity="sha384-QWTKZyjpPEjISv5WaRU9OFeRpok6YctnYmDr5pNlyT2bRjXh0JMhjY6hW+ALEwIH" crossorigin="anonymous">
  <title>Document</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/main.css">
</head>
<body>
  <%- include('partials/header') %> 
   

  <div class="container px-4 py-5" id="icon-grid">
    <h2 class="pb-2 border-bottom">Features of Web Application:</h2>

    <div class="row row-cols-1 row-cols-sm-2 row-cols-md-3 row-cols-lg-4 g-4 py-5">
      <div class="col d-flex align-items-start">
        <svg class="bi text-body-secondary flex-shrink-0 me-3" width="1.75em" height="1.75em"><use xlink:href="#bootstrap"></use></svg>
        <div>
          <h3 class="fw-bold mb-0 fs-4 text-body-emphasis">Trend Query Input</h3>
          <p>Users can input one or more queries (search terms) and submit them to fetch the trends data for those terms from Google Trends.
            The interface allows users to input multiple queries, such as "Pushpa", "Stree","Devara", etc., and view how their popularity varies over time.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col d-flex align-items-start">
        <svg class="bi text-body-secondary flex-shrink-0 me-3" width="1.75em" height="1.75em"><use xlink:href="#cpu-fill"></use></svg>
        <div>
          <h3 class="fw-bold mb-0 fs-4 text-body-emphasis">Trend Data Visualization</h3>
          <p>After submitting the queries, the site fetches data from Google Trends and displays it in a structured table.
            Each row of the table shows the date, the search query, its search volume value at that time, and the trend winner (i.e., the query with the highest value for a given date).</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col d-flex align-items-start">
        <svg class="bi text-body-secondary flex-shrink-0 me-3" width="1.75em" height="1.75em"><use xlink:href="#calendar3"></use></svg>
        <div>
          <h3 class="fw-bold mb-0 fs-4 text-body-emphasis">Dynamic Result Table</h3>
          <p>The trends data is dynamically displayed on the page, with queries, values, dates, and trend winners shown clearly.
            Trend Winners: The feature where the query with the highest value on a particular day is marked as the "winner," making it easy to spot which topic is leading.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col d-flex align-items-start">
        <svg class="bi text-body-secondary flex-shrink-0 me-3" width="1.75em" height="1.75em"><use xlink:href="#home"></use></svg>
        <div>
          <h3 class="fw-bold mb-0 fs-4 text-body-emphasis">CSV Download</h3>
          <p>The site provides a feature to download the results in a CSV format for further analysis or offline use.
            The CSV file contains data like date, queries, values, and the trend winner, which can be helpful for keeping records or analyzing trends outside the website.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col d-flex align-items-start">
        <svg class="bi text-body-secondary flex-shrink-0 me-3" width="1.75em" height="1.75em"><use xlink:href="#speedometer2"></use></svg>
        <div>
          <h3 class="fw-bold mb-0 fs-4 text-body-emphasis">Search History (Stored Queries)</h3>
          <p>When users query search terms and display results, the system remembers and displays the last searched queries, improving user experience by reducing the need to enter queries repeatedly.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
    </div>
  </div>

  
</body>
</html>